null}}, "cwe_ids": ["CWE-416"], "cwes": [{"cwe_id": "CWE-416", "name": "Use After Free"}], "description": "### Summary

_Short summary of the problem. Make the impact and severity as clear as possible._

The **HTTP OAuth2 filter** (`envoy.filters.http.oauth2`) can leave an **in-flight async token exchange** attached to a **downstream stream** that has already been torn down. A **late** `AsyncClient` completion can still invoke **`OAuth2Filter`** methods that use **`StreamDecoderFilterCallbacks`** after that object’s lifetime has ended, causing **undefined behavior**, **worker crashes (availability loss)**, and **use-after-free / invalid-vptr** failures under **AddressSanitizer**. This is a **memory-safety / lifetime (CWE-416–class)** issue in the data plane, not a trivial config bug. **Remote code execution is not claimed here**; the primary demonstrated impact is **DoS via crash** and **UB**; any further impact would be deployment- and allocator-dependent.

---

### Details

_Give all details on the vulnerability. Pointing to the incriminated source code is very helpful for the maintainer._

**Component:** `envoy.filters.http.oauth2` — `source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.{h,cc}`, `source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.{h,cc}`.

**Mechanism**

1. On the OAuth **authorization-code callback** path, **`OAuth2Filter`** calls **`OAuth2ClientImpl::asyncGetAccessToken`**, which issues an **async HTTP** request to the configured **token endpoint** and stops filter iteration until completion.
2. The **downstream stream** can be destroyed first (client **`RST_STREAM`**, disconnect, idle timeout, overload, etc.). **`StreamDecoderFilterCallbacks`** must not be used after teardown.
3. When the token HTTP response arrives, **`OAuth2ClientImpl::onSuccess`** (or **`onFailure`**) still forwards to the filter via **`parent_`** (the **`FilterCallbacks`** / **`OAuth2Filter`**), e.g. **`onGetAccessTokenSuccess`**, which eventually calls **`finishGetAccessTokenFlow()`** and uses **`decoder_callbacks_`**.

**Incriminated call chain (token success → encoder path)**

`OAuth2ClientImpl::onSuccess` ultimately does:

```cpp
// source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.cc
parent_->onGetAccessTokenSuccess(access_token, id_token, refresh_token, expires_in);
```

`OAuth2Filter::onGetAccessTokenSuccess` leads to **`finishGetAccessTokenFlow()`**, which calls into **`decoder_callbacks_`**:

```cpp
// source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.cc — finishGetAccessTokenFlow()
decoder_callbacks_->encodeHeaders(std::move(response_headers), true, REDIRECT_LOGGED_IN);
```

If **`decoder_callbacks_`** no longer refers to a live object, this virtual call is **unsafe** (UAF / invalid vptr class under sanitizers).

**Root cause (conceptual, pre-fix)**

- Stream teardown did not **cancel** the in-flight OAuth **`AsyncClient`** request and did not make **`OAuth2ClientImpl`** treat **`parent_`** as **invalid** after teardown, so **late completions** could still run filter callback code.

---

### PoC

_Complete instructions, including specific configuration details, to reproduce the vulnerability._  
_These steps assume an **unfixed** Envoy (no fix patch applied). Use an **ASAN** build for a deterministic sanitizer report._

#### A — Runtime / configuration

1. **Build** Envoy from source at a vulnerable revision, **with AddressSanitizer** (see Envoy docs: e.g. Linux `bazel build -c dbg --config=asan`; macOS: use your repo’s ASAN-capable Bazel config).
2. **Configure** a listener with **`envoy.filters.http.oauth2`**, valid **authorization** and **redirect** settings, and a **`token_endpoint`** cluster you can make **slow** (mock IdP, injected latency, `delay` in front of the token service, etc.).
3. **Drive** a real client through the OAuth **callback** so the filter **starts** the async token exchange and waits on the token response.
4. **Tear down** the downstream stream **before** the token HTTP response completes: HTTP/2 **`RST_STREAM`**, browser tab close, short **stream idle timeout**, or **concurrent** traffic so resets interleave with in-flight token requests.
5. **Observe** worker **crash** or ASAN / UBSan output implicating **`OAuth2Filter::finishGetAccessTokenFlow`** / **`onGetAccessTokenSuccess`** / **`encodeHeaders`**.

#### B — Unit test (deterministic harness)

Add the following as a **temporary** test in **`//test/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter_test.cc`** (same style as existing `OAuth2Test` tests: `init(...)`, mock validator, mock OAuth client). Run only under **ASAN**; **remove** the test after validation. It does **not** require applying the fix patch.

```cpp
// TEMPORARY PoC only — delete after triage. ASAN build required.
TEST_F(OAuth2Test, PoC_LateTokenSuccessAfterDecoderCallbacksFreed) {
#if defined(WIN32)
  GTEST_SKIP();
#elif defined(__SANITIZE_ADDRESS__) || defined(ADDRESS_SANITIZER) || \
    (defined(__has_feature) && __has_feature(address_sanitizer))
  init(getConfig(false /* forward_bearer_token */, true /* use_refresh_token */));
  test_time_.setSystemTime(SystemTime(std::chrono::seconds(1000)));

  Http::TestRequestHeaderMapImpl request_headers{
      {Http::Headers::get().Path.get(), "/_oauth?code=123&state=" + TEST_ENCODED_STATE},
      {Http::Headers::get().Cookie.get(),
       "OauthNonce=" + TEST_CSRF_TOKEN + ";path=/;Max-Age=600;secure;HttpOnly"},
      {Http::Headers::get().Cookie.get(),
       "CodeVerifier=" + TEST_ENCRYPTED_CODE_VERIFIER + ";path=/;Max-Age=600;secure;HttpOnly"},
      {Http::Headers::get().Host.get(), "traffic.example.com"},
      {Http::Headers::get().Scheme.get(), "https"},
      {Http::Headers::get().Method.get(), Http::Headers::get().MethodValues.Get},
  };

  EXPECT_CALL(*validator_, setParams(_, _));
  EXPECT_CALL(*validator_, isValid()).WillOnce(Return(false));
  EXPECT_CALL(*oauth_client_, asyncGetAccessToken("123", TEST_CLIENT_ID, "asdf_client_secret_fdsa",
                                                  "https://traffic.example.com" + TEST_CALLBACK,
                                                  TEST_CODE_VERIFIER, AuthType::UrlEncodedBody));

  EXPECT_EQ(Http::FilterHeadersStatus::StopAllIterationAndBuffer,
            filter_->decodeHeaders(request_headers, false));

  auto* doomed = new NiceMock<Http::MockStreamDecoderFilterCallbacks>();
  filter_->setDecoderFilterCallbacks(*doomed);
  delete doomed;

  // Vulnerable: late completion uses dangling decoder_callbacks_.
  filter_->onGetAccessTokenSuccess("access_code", "some-id-token", "some-refresh-token",
                                   std::chrono::seconds(600));
#else
  GTEST_SKIP() << "ASAN-only";
#endif
}
```

**Run (example):**

```bash
bazel test //test/extensions/filters/http/oauth2:filter_test -c dbg --config=asan \
  --test_filter='OAuth2Test.PoC_LateTokenSuccessAfterDecoderCallbacksFreed' \
  --test_output=all
```

Expect a **sanitizer failure** (e.g. invalid vptr / heap-use-after-free) on **`decoder_callbacks_->encodeHeaders`**.

---

### Impact

_What kind of vulnerability is it? Who is impacted?_

| | |
| --- | --- |
| **Kind** | **CWE-416** (use-after-free) / **lifetime bug** between **HTTP stream teardown** and **async OAuth token completion**; manifests as **undefined behavior** and **worker crash (DoS)**. |
| **Who is impacted** | Deployments using **`envoy.filters.http.oauth2`** where downstream streams can disappear **while the token endpoint request is still in flight** (slow IdP, timeouts, HTTP/2 resets, high churn). |
| **Attacker / exposure** | Any remote client that can open OAuth flows and reset or close streams during the token leg; no special credentials implied. |
| **RCE** | **Not asserted** in this report; primary impact is **availability** and **memory safety** of the proxy worker. |

---

### Possible fix 

_What to change and how to apply the minimal fix._

**Intent**

1. **`OAuth2Filter::onDestroy()`** — call **`oauth_client_->cancel()`** and clear **`request_headers_`** so teardown drops in-flight token work and does not leave dangling request state.
2. **`OAuth2Client::cancel()`** — cancel **`in_flight_request_`**, reset **`OAuthState`**, set **`parent_ = nullptr`**.
3. **`OAuth2ClientImpl::onSuccess` / `onFailure`** — if **`parent_ == nullptr`**, return immediately (late callback after cancel/teardown).

**Minimal patch file (production only, four files):**

```
diff --git a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.cc b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.cc
index 45affb1a59..836e629059 100644
--- a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.cc
+++ b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.cc
@@ -567,6 +567,13 @@ OAuth2Filter::OAuth2Filter(FilterConfigSharedPtr config,
   oauth_client_->setCallbacks(*this);
 }
 
+void OAuth2Filter::onDestroy() {
+  // Drop any in-flight async token exchange before the stream tears down; otherwise a late
+  // AsyncClient callback can invoke decoder callbacks on a destroyed stream.
+  oauth_client_->cancel();
+  request_headers_ = nullptr;
+}
+
 /**
  * primary cases:
  * 1) pass through header is matching
diff --git a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.h b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.h
index 3f5e6f6b5b..95aea737e5 100644
--- a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.h
+++ b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/filter.h
@@ -320,6 +320,7 @@ public:
   // Http::PassThroughFilter
   Http::FilterHeadersStatus decodeHeaders(Http::RequestHeaderMap& headers, bool) override;
   Http::FilterHeadersStatus encodeHeaders(Http::ResponseHeaderMap& headers, bool) override;
+  void onDestroy() override;
 
   // FilterCallbacks
   void onGetAccessTokenSuccess(const std::string& access_code, const std::string& id_token,
diff --git a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.cc b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.cc
index 13f6d40f83..538228cac3 100644
--- a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.cc
+++ b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.cc
@@ -107,6 +107,15 @@ void OAuth2ClientImpl::asyncRefreshAccessToken(const std::string& refresh_token,
   dispatchRequest(std::move(request));
 }
 
+void OAuth2ClientImpl::cancel() {
+  if (in_flight_request_ != nullptr) {
+    in_flight_request_->cancel();
+    in_flight_request_ = nullptr;
+  }
+  state_ = OAuthState::Idle;
+  parent_ = nullptr;
+}
+
 void OAuth2ClientImpl::dispatchRequest(Http::RequestMessagePtr&& msg) {
   const auto thread_local_cluster = cm_.getThreadLocalCluster(uri_.cluster());
   if (thread_local_cluster != nullptr) {
@@ -129,6 +138,11 @@ void OAuth2ClientImpl::onSuccess(const Http::AsyncClient::Request&,
                                  Http::ResponseMessagePtr&& message) {
   in_flight_request_ = nullptr;
 
+  if (parent_ == nullptr) {
+    state_ = OAuthState::Idle;
+    return;
+  }
+
   ASSERT(state_ == OAuthState::PendingAccessToken ||
          state_ == OAuthState::PendingAccessTokenByRefreshToken);
   const OAuthState oldState = state_;
@@ -206,6 +220,12 @@ void OAuth2ClientImpl::onFailure(const Http::AsyncClient::Request&,
                                  Http::AsyncClient::FailureReason) {
   ENVOY_LOG(debug, "OAuth request failed.");
   in_flight_request_ = nullptr;
+
+  if (parent_ == nullptr) {
+    state_ = OAuthState::Idle;
+    return;
+  }
+
   const OAuthState oldState = state_;
   state_ = OAuthState::Idle;
 
diff --git a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.h b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.h
index 16ba6e2105..a5124a61bf 100644
--- a/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.h
+++ b/source/extensions/filters/http/oauth2/oauth_client.h
@@ -37,6 +37,12 @@ public:
                                        const std::string& client_id, const std::string& secret,
                                        AuthType auth_type = AuthType::UrlEncodedBody) PURE;
 
+  /**
+   * Cancels any in-flight async token request. After this returns, callbacks must not touch the
+   * owning filter (typically invoked from OAuth2Filter::onDestroy()).
+   */
+  virtual void cancel() PURE;
+
   virtual void setCallbacks(FilterCallbacks& callbacks) PURE;
 
   // Http::AsyncClient::Callbacks
@@ -52,11 +58,7 @@ public:
                    const std::chrono::seconds default_expires_in)
       : cm_(cm), uri_(uri), retry_policy_(retry_policy), default_expires_in_(default_expires_in) {}
 
-  ~OAuth2ClientImpl() override {
-    if (in_flight_request_ != nullptr) {
-      in_flight_request_->cancel();
-    }
-  }
+  ~OAuth2ClientImpl() override { cancel(); }
 
   // OAuth2Client
   /**
@@ -69,6 +71,8 @@ public:
   void asyncRefreshAccessToken(const std::string& refresh_token, const std::string& client_id,
                                const std::string& secret, AuthType auth_type) override;
 
+  void cancel() override;
+
   void setCallbacks(FilterCallbacks& callbacks) override { parent_ = &callbacks; }
 
   // AsyncClient::Callbacks

```




